iopair.name: C-C191B-GREP-01-ST04-DT02-DF11-CF20-01-GOOD-01
iopair.description: all words beginning with e or x, case sensitive Reads in a file and determines its size. If the size is less than 128, checked by a '(max_size - size_of_file) > 0', the file will be read into a buffer of that size and printed out. An integer underflow can occur if the file is large enough causing a >0 check to pass that should not. This will cause an overwrite within the fread() function, resulting in Segmentation fault
